g.text: All these models have traditionally been in use within the European Union (EU). The European Directive
on unfair contract terms attempts to combine them with irritating and partially even unexpected effects
on national laws. However, the Directive has increased the transparency of the European system.
A useful role for a principle of fairness is nowadays recognized even for business-to-business
agreements in a European and global context. Arbitrators certainly look at the reasonableness of the
outcome, even though the reasoning often is dressed in a more formalist language. Again, an express
fairness reasoning might more transparently address the issues at hand.
